# Docki Template

This is a template for a new docki documentation repository. It contains

* a few example `*.adoc` files in the [`./docs`](docs) folder
* a config file [`docki.config.toml`](docki.config.toml) with all the default settings
* a [`.github/workflows/docki_pages_publish.yml`](.github/workflows/docki_pages_publish.yml) file for publishing the docs to GitHub Pages

## Building Process

![directory structure](./.github/assets/directory_structure.png)

1. Will be converted into asciidoc format
2. Will be converted into asciidocs slides


## Setup GH Pages

This template icontains a workflow for publishing the docs to GitHub Pages. This only works if Github Pages is enabled for the repository. Below are instructions on how to enable it.

![go to settings](./.github/assets/step_1.png)
![go to gh pages settings](./.github/assets/step_2.png)
![open source dropdown](./.github/assets/step_3.png)
![select gh actions as source](./.github/assets/step_4.png)

## Building locally

To build the docs locally, i would recommend checking out the [docki](https://github.com/quirinecker/docki) repository iteself. It offers instructions on how to install and use docki.
